      • addModule

        public AppInfoBundle.Builder addModule(@NonNull
                                       java.lang.String moduleName,
                                       @Nullable
                                       java.lang.String version,
                                       @Nullable
                                       java.lang.String description)
        Constructs a Module instance using the given module name. Additional Module.Component objects can be appended to this module by calling addComponent(Module.Type, String, String, String, String).

        Modules are considered to be a grouping of Module.Component objects that are necessary for a specific piece of functionality to work (e.g., ASR config files, wrapper library, etc.).

        Parameters:
        moduleName - The name of the module.
        version - A version number associated with the module. This can be null.
        description - A description of the module if applicable. This can be null.
        Returns:
        This builder instance.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - Thrown if the provided module name is null.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if the provided module name is an empty string.

      • addComponent

        public AppInfoBundle.Builder addComponent(@NonNull
                                          Module.Type type,
                                          @NonNull
                                          java.lang.String name,
                                          @Nullable
                                          java.lang.String locale,
                                          @Nullable
                                          java.lang.String version,
                                          @Nullable
                                          java.lang.String description)

        Constructs a Module.Component object using the provided parameters and attaches it to the last Module instance that was creating using addModule(String, String, String).

        Components are general purpose descriptors of the parent modules. Usually, they represent components that are necessary for the Module to function and usually have their own versioning information.

        Parameters:
        type - A Module.Type associated with this property.
        name - A name for the property.
        version - A semantic version number to associate with this property if applicable.
        description - A more general description of the property if desired.
        Returns:
        This builder instance.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - Thrown if a addModule(String, String, String) has not been called prior to this method. Also called if the provided type and/or name are null.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if the provided type and/or name are empty strings.
